definition.value: A piperidine that is 3-methyl-2,4-dioxo-3,4-dihydropyrimidine carrying additional 2-cyanobenzyl and 3-aminopiperidin-1-yl groups at positions 1 and 2 respectively (the R-enantiomer). Used in the form of its benzoate salt for treatment of type 2 diabetes.
A benzoate salt obtained by combining equimolar amounts of alogliptin and benzoic acid. Used for treatment of type 2 diabetes.
Any organic salt prepared using benzoic acid as the acid component.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the primary amino function of alogliptin.
An amino trisaccharide comprising two alpha-sialyl residues joined by a (2->8)-linkage and attached in turn by a (2->8)-linkage to a third sialyl residue of unspecified anomeric configuration.
alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-Neup5Ac in which the sialyl residue at the reducing end has alpha anomeric configuration.
A 2',3'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is GMP in which the hydroxy groups at the 2' and 3' positions have been converted into the corresponding cyclic phosphate.
A 3-oxo Delta(4)-steroid that is campest-4-en-3-one bearing an additional 22S-hydroxy substituent.
A brassinosteroid that is campesterol bearing an additional 22S-hydroxy substituent.

An imidazochromene that is 1,7,8,9-tetrahydrochromeno[5,6-d]imidazol-2-amine bearing additional 3-(dimethylamino)propyl and (dimethylamino)methyl substituents at positions 1 and 8 respectively (the R-enantiomer).
An organic heterotricyclic compound that consists of a chromene ring system having an imidazole ring ortho-fused at any position.
A glycophytoceramide having an alpha-D-galactopyranosyl residue at the O-1 position and a palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) group attached to the nitrogen.
A group of heterocyclic compounds based on the 5,6-dihydropteroic acid skeleton conjugated with one or more L-glutamic acid units.
A trideoxyhexose derivative that is alpha-D-glucose in which the 2 and 6-hydroxy groups are replaced by amino groups while the 3-hydroxy group is replaced by hydrogen.
A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine having sulfo groups at the 3- and 6-positions on the galactose ring and lauroyl (dodecanoyl) as the N-acyl group.

A disaccharide derivative consisting of a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranonosyl unit joined via an alpha-(2->4)-linkage to a 5,6-dehydro-3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranonosyl unit with an O-allyl group at the anomeric centre.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the amino groups of 2,6-diamino-2,3,6-trideoxy-alpha-D-glucose.
An aminodiol that is cyclohexane-1,2-diol substituted at positions 3 and 5 by amino groups (the 1S,2S,3R,5S-diastereomer)

An L-alpha-amino acid that is L-serine in which the hydroxy group at position 3 is converted to the corresponding 2-aminoethyl ether. An antimetabolic antibiotic obtained from Streptomyces reseoviridofuscus.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the amino groups of (1S,2S,3R,5S)-3,5-diaminocyclohexane-1,2-diol
A 3-amino-3-deoxy-D-glucopyranose that has alpha-configuration at the anomeric position.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the amino group of alpha-D-kanosamine.
An  organochlorine compound that is 7H-purin-2-amine substituted by a chloro group at position 6.
A benzopteridine that is riboflavin in which the methyl group at position 8 is substituted by a dimethylamino group.
